		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Xerox Alto</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:242px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Xerox_Alto.jpg" class="image" title="The Xerox Alto monitor has a portrait orientation."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Xerox_Alto.jpg/240px-Xerox_Alto.jpg" width="240" height="320" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Xerox_Alto.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The Xerox Alto monitor has a portrait orientation.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>Xerox Alto</b> was an early <a href="/wiki/Personal_computer" title="Personal computer">personal computer</a> developed at <a href="/wiki/Xerox_PARC" title="Xerox PARC" class="mw-redirect">Xerox PARC</a> in 1973. It was the first computer to use the <a href="/wiki/Desktop_metaphor" title="Desktop metaphor">desktop metaphor</a> and <a href="/wiki/Graphical_user_interface" title="Graphical user interface">graphical user interface</a> (GUI).</p>
<p>It was not a commercial product, but several thousand units were built and were heavily used at PARC and at several universities for many years. The Alto greatly influenced the design of personal computers in the following decades, notably the <a href="/wiki/Apple_Macintosh" title="Apple Macintosh" class="mw-redirect">Macintosh</a> and the first <a href="/wiki/Sun_Microsystems" title="Sun Microsystems">Sun</a> workstations. It is now very rare and a valuable collector's item.</p>
